This paper is about a programming language (GP 2) and its design goals of simplicity and formal reasoning. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses program verification, which falls under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the use of graph transformation rules suggests a connection to Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
